EDUCATION STATE BOARD OF EDUCATION Notice of Intended Regulatory Action Notice is hereby given in accordance with Â§ 9-6.14:7.1 of the Code of Virginia that the State Board of Education intends to consider amending regulations entitled: 8 VAC 20-131-10 et seq.
Regulations Establishing Standards for Accrediting Public Schools in Virginia.
The purpose of the proposed action is to incorporate new language as required by Â§ 22.1253.13:4 F of the Code of Virginia (enacted by the 1998 Session of the General Assembly) which requires the State Board of Education to develop criteria for recognizing exemplary performance in vocational studies by students who have completed the requirements for a standard or advanced studies diploma and to award seals on the diploma of students meeting such criteria.
The agency intends to hold a public hearing on the proposed action after publication.
