Notice is hereby given in accordance with Â§ 9-6.14:7.1 of the Code of Virginia that the State Water Control Board intends to consider amending regulations entitled: 9 VAC 25-260-10 et seq.
Water Quality Standards.
The purpose of the proposed action is to consider whether the board should amend the Upper James River Basin section tables to correct the stream classification of a small section of the Jackson River in Alleghany County.
The rulemaking, if adopted, will correctly classify the section from a Class V, stockable trout water, to a Class IV, mountainous zone water.
